\begin_layout Standard
Ruby and Sapphire are celebrating Pi Day by sharing a circular pie.
 Ruby has two red birthday cake candles, and Sapphire has two blue candles.
 Ruby starting, they will alternately place one candle on the perimeter
 of the pie.
 (Of course, no two candles may be in the same place!) After all the candles
 are placed, each girl will get the portion of the pie that is closer to
 one of her candles than to any of the others.
 The goal is to get strictly more pie than one’s opponent; an equal division
 is a draw.
\end_layout

